{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 TJF Smart Fade (similar behavior to Protools)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This script mimics certain fade behaviors from protools based on time selection, Razor Edit, or Item Selection. It is a bit contextual, and behaves slightly different based on which tool you are using (time/razor/item selection) I recommend working in a protools style mode with Autocrossfade off and Cut Behind Items enabled\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 DEFAULT FADE LENGTH: This script has a default fade length and allows you to set the default fadeshapes for normal fades as well as scrossfades These settings can be adjusted in GLOBAL VARIABLES\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Thanks to BirdBird and Amagalma for chunks of this code as well as inspiration for learning some techniques to make this script possible\par}
}

